es/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>12. We find advertising on the radio <em>very</em> effective.</div><div>13. Two students were penalized <em>very</em> differently for the same offence.</div><div>14. I've never been <em>very</em> good at arithmetic.</div><div>15. I felt <em>very</em> inferior among all those academics.</div><div>16. She's <em>very</em> conventional in her views.</div><div>17. I'm not <em>very</em> popular with my parents at the moment.</div><div>18. I'm <em>very</em> optimistic about our chances of success.</div><div>19. <em>Very</em> few students learn Latin now.</div><div>20. "It's <em>very</em> difficult, " I said. "Impossible, " she chimed in.</div><div>21. My leg is still <em>very</em> tender where it was bruised.</div><div>22. The teacher's voice is <em>very</em> loud;we can all hear it.</div><div>23. The clothes blend with her color of skin <em>very</em> much.</div><div>24. Be careful not to overextend yourself. You've been <em>very</em> ill.</div><div>25. When the weasel and the cat make a marriage, it is a <em>very</em> ill presage.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42285.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>26. Poverty is an abnormality to rich people. It is <em>very</em> difficult to make out why people who want dinner do not ring the bell.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47091.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>27. He who laughs at crooked men should need walk <em>very</em> straight.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41120.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>28. To be angry with a weak man is a proof that you are not <em>very</em> strong yourself.&nbsp;<a href='/s/44015.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>29. All good things are cheap, all bad things are <em>very</em> dear.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47010.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30. Donna might be able to come tomorrow, but it's <em>very</em> unlikely .</div></div><!--all结束-->  <!--如果不是仅显示学生,或该页没有学生句子-->  <div id="student" style='display:none;'>  <div>1. The competition is <em>very</em> strong this time.</div><div>2. Be careful not to overextend yourself. You've been <em>very</em> ill.</div><div>3. The police are <em>very</em> concerned for the welfare of the missing child.</div><div>4. His plots are always <em>very</em> ingenious.</div><div>5. She wears glasses with <em>very</em> thick lenses.</div><div>6. I can't hear you <em>very</em> well.</div><div>7. I know <em>very</em> little about him.</div><div>8. I should add that we are <em>very</em> lucky.</div><div>9. I'm told I have a <em>very</em> pronounced English accent when I speak French.</div><div>9. Sentencedict.com is a online sentence dictionary, on which you can find good sentences for a large number of words.</div><div>10. They've furnished the room <em>very</em> simply.</div><div>11. I enjoyed reading these books <em>very</em> much.</div><div>12. She is a <em>very</em> domestic sort of woman.</div><div>13. She was <em>very</em> shy while she was in elementary school.</div><div>14. We are <em>very</em> pleased to have the opportunity to...</div><div>15. We welcome this development <em>very</em> much.</div><div>16. He was <em>very</em> cautious about committing himself to anything.</div><div>17. I appreciate <em>very</em> much that you...</div><div>18. We <em>very</em> much regret to have to remind you of...</div><div>19. He is <em>very</em> aggressive in many ways.</div><div>20. Thank you <em>very</em> much for your cooperation.</div><div>21. The old lady is <em>very</em> cautious with her money.</div